  "prompt": "Why do I get snapchat notifications of some people but not others?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you receive Snapchat notifications from some people but not others:\n\n1. **Notification Settings**: Check your notification settings both within Snapchat and on your phone. Snapchat allows you to customize notifications for different types of activities and individual friends. Make sure notifications are enabled for all friends if you want to receive updates from everyone.\n\n2. **Do Not Disturb**: If you\u2019ve enabled Do Not Disturb for specific friends or in general, it could prevent notifications from coming through.\n\n3. **Muting Friends**: You might have muted notifications for specific friends. To check this, go to the chat screen, press and hold on a friend's name, and then see if the \"Notification\" setting indicates whether they are muted.\n\n4. **App-Specific Settings**: Ensure that Snapchat itself has the necessary permissions on your phone to send notifications. Sometimes app-specific settings might interfere with this.\n\n5. **Phone Settings**: Your phone\u2019s settings, such as battery optimization modes, might restrict background activities and notifications for specific apps.\n\n6. **Snapchat Updates**: Occasionally, app updates or bugs might affect notification settings. Ensure that your app is up-to-date and consider reinstalling if necessary.\n\n7. **Snapchat Algorithm**: Snapchat might prioritize notifications differently based on engagement levels. If you interact with certain friends more than others, Snapchat might send you more frequent notifications about them.\n\nReview these aspects to troubleshoot why you're receiving notifications from some people but not others.",
